This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of multiview stereo, which is a common task in computer vision. Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for 3D dense reconstruction, which is a popular research area in computer vision. 

The paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with the problem of generating 3D models from multiple images, which is a common task in computer graphics. 

The robotics (cs.RO) sub-category is also a possibility as 3D reconstruction is an important task in robotics, especially for tasks such as mapping and localization. 

The multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is another possibility as 3D reconstruction is also important in multimedia applications such as virtual reality and augmented reality. 

Finally, the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category is a possibility as the paper proposes a new method for joint view selection, which involves the use of a cost matrix and inference, both of which are common techniques in machine learning.
